Package org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords

Class TimeStamp

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords.Coordinate
      • org.ivoa.dm.stc.coords.TimeStamp
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulations
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TimeInstant, TimeOffset
    @Embeddable
@VoDml(id="coords:TimeStamp",
       role=dataType)
public abstract class TimeStamp
extends Coordinate
implements org.ivoa.vodml.jpa.JPAManipulations
    This is the abstract basis for a set of simple time domain coordinates which are expected to accommodate the vast majority of use cases. All TimeStamps, by definition, exist in a standard 1-D coordinate space, with domainMin|Max of +/-Infinity. All TimeStamps MUST refer to an appropriate TimeSys. dataType: TimeStamp
